prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "The system never terminates but idles in a waiting state when the pump is not operating.",
      "evidence_quote": "Notice that this system never terminates but idles in a waiting state when the pump is not operating."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "The buyer can insert a credit card into a card reader built into the pump.",
      "evidence_quote": "The buyer inserts a credit card into a card reader built into the pump."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "The system reads card details when the credit card is inserted.",
      "evidence_quote": "This causes a transition to a Reading state where the card details are read"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "The buyer can remove the credit card from the card reader.",
      "evidence_quote": "Removal of the card triggers a transition to a Validating state"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "The system validates the inserted credit card.",
      "evidence_quote": "If the card is valid, the system initializes the pump"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "The system initializes the pump when the credit card is validated.",
      "evidence_quote": "If the card is valid, the system initializes the pump and, when the fuel hose is removed from its holster..."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "The system transitions to the Delivering state when the fuel hose is removed from its holster.",
      "evidence_quote": "...transitions to the Delivering state, where it is ready to deliver fuel"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Fuel delivery starts when the trigger on the nozzle is activated.",
      "evidence_quote": "Activating the trigger on the nozzle causes fuel to be pumped"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Fuel delivery stops when the trigger on the nozzle is released.",
      "evidence_quote": "...stops when the trigger is released (for simplicity, I have ignored the pressure switch that is designed to stop fuel spillage)"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "The system transitions to the Paying state after fuel delivery is complete.",
      "evidence_quote": "After the fuel delivery is complete and the buyer has replaced the hose in its holster..."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "The user's account is debited when payment is made.",
      "evidence_quote": "...the system moves to a Paying state where the user’s account is debited"
    }
  ]
}

